# === Fingerprint determinism patches ===
# These exclude package directories that produce different hashes between
# local installs and EAS Build's recompute. Without them, the `fingerprint`
# runtime version policy fails the build's CONFIGURE_EXPO_UPDATES phase with
# 'Runtime version calculated on local machine not equal to runtime version
# calculated during build'.

# expo-modules-jsi: podspec `prepare_command` stamps machine-specific stub
# binaries into Products/ during `pod install`. Different machines + different
# pod install runs produce different Info.plist content. The package's source
# Swift/C++ files outside Products/ are still hashed, so a real package
# upgrade still bumps the fingerprint.
node_modules/expo-modules-jsi/apple/Products/**

# react-native-reanimated + react-native-worklets: their `apple/` directories
# hash differently across bun versions (1.3.14 local vs 1.3.8 on EAS Build),
# even with `--frozen-lockfile` and identical package versions. Root cause
# not fully identified; safest broad exclusion until upstream determinism
# fix lands. package.json bumps to either lib are still hashed (via the
# package's metadata) so version upgrades still trigger fingerprint changes.
node_modules/react-native-reanimated/apple/**
node_modules/react-native-worklets/apple/**
